As Amended by House Committee
Session of 2025
SENATE BILL No. 6
By Committee on Federal and State Affairs
1-14
1 AN ACT concerning elections; prohibiting the use of any form of ranked-
2 choice voting methods in conducting elections.
3
4 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
5 Section 1. (a) No form of ranked-choice voting method shall be used
6 in determining the election or nomination of any candidate to any federal,
7 state, county or other municipal elected office.
8 (b) As used in this section, the term "ranked-choice voting" means a
9 form of voting that allows voters to rank two or more candidates for an
10 elected office in order of preference and tabulates the cast ballots in
11 multiple rounds with the elimination of the lowest vote-receiving
12 candidate after each round until a candidate receives a majority of the
13 votes cast.
14 (c) Any ordinance, resolution or regulation prohibited by subsection
15 (a) that was adopted prior to July 1, 2025, shall be null and void.
16 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
17 publication in the statute book Kansas register.

